\begin{slide}
\section{Solution to Fokker-Planck}

\begin{PauseHighLight}
  \begin{itemize}
  \item I cheated, this is actually the solution to the Markov
    chain\pause
  \item However, the Fokker-Planck provides the same information and
    would provide an almost identical outcome\pause
  \item The Markov chain solution is exact (it does not make the
    assumption of continuous time or that $X(t)$ is a continuous
    variable)\pause
  \item But the Fokker-Planck equation provides a near identical
    solution, but is solvable for any $P$ (Markov chain analysis becomes
    too slow to solve for large $P$)\pause
  \end{itemize}
\end{PauseHighLight}

\end{slide}



